content:
CRM Analytics requires access to Salesforce data when extracting the data and also when the data is used as part of row-level security. CRM Analytics gains access to Salesforce data based on permissions of two internal CRM Analytics users: Integration User and Security User.

The Integration User uses permissions to extract data from Salesforce objects and fields when a dataflow job runs, so consider restricting access to particular objects and fields that contain sensitive data. If the dataflow is configured to extract data from an object or field on which the Integration User does not have permission, the dataflow job fails.

When querying a dataset that has row-level security based on the User object, CRM Analytics uses the permissions of the Security User to access the User object and its fields. The Security User must have at least read permission on each User object field included in a predicate. A predicate is a filter condition that defines row-level security for a dataset.

Do not delete either the Integration User or the Security User because CRM Analytics requires their access to Salesforce data. Configure the permissions of the Integration User and Security User to control access to Salesforce objects and fields.
title: CRM Analytics Data Access and Permissions
